    <h1 class=" text-center text-3xl font-extrabold leading-tight text-black my-6">
        About this Tool
    </h1>
    <div class="about">
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
            The <strong>Assamese Text Annotation Tool</strong> is a comprehensive platform built to assist linguists, researchers, and developers in the annotation of Assamese-language texts. It supports both manual and AI-assisted tagging for various Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks, making it easier to create high-quality datasets for training models.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
            The tool primarily focuses on <strong>Named Entity Recognition (NER)</strong> and <strong>Coreference Resolution</strong>, allowing users to identify and label entities such as names, places, and organizations. It also provides a user-friendly interface to manage annotations—add, modify, or delete them with ease—offering flexibility throughout the annotation process.
          </p>
        
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-700 mt-6 mb-3">Key Features</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 text-base space-y-2">
            <li><strong>NER Tagging:</strong> Highlight words or phrases and assign categories like <em>PERSON</em>, <em>LOCATION</em>, or <em>LANGUAGE</em>.</li>
            <li><strong>Annotation Management:</strong> Edit or remove tags with intuitive controls.</li>
            <li><strong>Download Annotations:</strong> Export your annotations in a structured format (e.g., JSON) for training or analysis.</li>
            <li><strong>Coreference Clustering:</strong> Group related mentions together and visualize relationships across sentences.</li>
            <li><strong>AI Assistance:</strong> Use pre-trained models to auto-suggest entities for faster annotation.</li>
          </ul>
        
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mt-6">
            By streamlining the annotation workflow and supporting rich features tailored to the Assamese language, this tool plays a vital role in advancing regional NLP research and applications.
          </p>
